# Native build products
*.o
*.obj
*.dll
*.exe
*.exp
*.lib
*.pdb
*.ilk
*.so
*.dylib

# Vendored binaries we deliberately commit. ripgrep ships in the
# Flutter asset bundle so SEARCH_TEXT works for colleagues without
# requiring a manual `winget install BurntSushi.ripgrep.MSVC` /
# `brew install ripgrep`. See lib/services/ripgrep_provisioner.dart
# for the runtime-extraction flow.
!assets/bin/**

# OS junk
Thumbs.db
Desktop.ini

# Python scratch/cache files if helper scripts are added
__pycache__/
*.py[cod]
.pytest_cache/
.mypy_cache/
.ruff_cache/
.venv/
venv/

# AGENTS.md and CLAUDE.md are intentionally tracked — they hold the
# GitNexus integration block (managed by `npx gitnexus analyze`) plus
# any project-wide agent rules. Ignoring them would leave fresh
# clones / new collaborators without GitNexus context until they
# re-ran the installer. Don't add them here without a concrete
# reason; they're meant to ship with the repo.

# Defensive: SQLite scratch / journal files if any future feature
# starts caching to disk. Today nothing writes these; keeping the
# rule means a future addition won't accidentally commit a half-
# written DB.
*.sqlite
*.sqlite-journal
*.db
CLAUDE.md
AGENTS.md